18/01/2005
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- During a visit to Belgrade on Monday (17 January), UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen pledged to investigate the problem of power supply cuts to Serb settlements in Kosovo. The issue was raised as a priority during separate talks with Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica and President Boris Tadic. The UNMIK chief said his adviser would visit the villages in question to assess the situation. (Danas - 18/01/05; Beta, B92, Tanjug - 17/01/05)
